  "time_ut": 1661341165,
  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0bb9\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0ba3\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bbe\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0bb5\u0bb4\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 13 \u0bae\u0bc1\u0bb1\u0bc8 \u0b92\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb5\u0bc8\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Hirunika's case was adjourned 13 times",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Colombo High Court Judge Amal Ranaraja announced today (24) that the further evidentiary hearing of the case filed against former Member of Parliament Hirunika Premachandra will take place on the 16th of November in connection with the incident of abducting and assaulting a young man in Themattakodai area of \u200b\u200bColombo.",
        "When the case was taken up today (24), counsel appearing for Hirunika announced in the court to announce another day for further evidence hearing as her senior counsel Ashan Fernando is unwell.",
        "At that time, Deputy Solicitor General Janaka Bhandara, who appeared for the complainant, informed the court that although it was taken up for evidentiary hearing in 2017, it was postponed due to various reasons and therefore the evidentiary hearing should be started soon.",
        "Colombo High Court Judge Amal Ranaraja, who considered the arguments of both sides, pointed out in open court that the evidence hearing has been adjourned for almost the 13th time and announced November 16 as the day for further evidence hearing.",
        "On December 21, 2015, a case was filed by the Attorney General against Hirunika and 9 people including his bodyguards in connection with the incident of abducting a youth in Tematagoda area in a Defender type vehicle owned by Hirunika MP.",
        "Enmar has confessed his guilt in the case and the Hirunika MP has denied the allegations against him. He was acquitted because one of the eight was a school student under the age of 18 (the 8th accused).",
        "Apart from Hirunika Premachandra and a school student, the seven other accused who confessed to the crime were sentenced to 2 years of rigorous imprisonment suspended for 12 years by the Colombo High Court.",
        "Apart from the 2nd and 8th convicts, six were fined Rs 32,000 each and ordered to pay compensation of Rs 285,000 to the victim."
      ],
